# Kerry Hanson Portfolio — Cursor Rules

## Project overview

Personal UX designer portfolio built with React 19, Vite 7, React Router, Tailwind CSS v4, and Lucide React. Deployed on Vercel.

## Stack and conventions

- Use JavaScript (`.jsx` / `.js`), not TypeScript.
- Use Tailwind utility classes plus existing `theme-*` CSS utilities from `src/index.css`.
- Use Lucide React for icons. Brand icons (e.g. LinkedIn) are not available in lucide-react 1.x — use generic icons like `Link2`.
- Prefer functional components and hooks. Keep components focused and colocated under `src/components/`, pages under `src/pages/`.

## Theming

- Four themes: `light`, `soft`, `dusk`, `dark` — defined via `[data-theme]` CSS variables in `src/index.css`.
- Always use theme-aware classes (`theme-text`, `theme-surface`, `theme-accent`, `theme-border`, etc.) instead of hardcoded colors so all themes stay in sync.
- Theme state lives in `src/context/ThemeContext.jsx` and persists to `localStorage`.
- When adding or changing colors, update **all four themes** and verify WCAG 2.2 AA contrast (see Accessibility below).
- Key tokens: `--color-text-muted`, `--color-text-subtle`, `--color-link`, `--color-btn-primary-fg`, `--color-indicator-inactive`, `--color-badge-bg`, `--color-badge-text`.

## Content and data

- Profile/resume content: `src/data/profile.js`
- Project case studies: `src/data/projects.js` — add optional `image`, `imageAlt`, `imageWidth`, `imageHeight` for real screenshots
- Hero slider config: `src/config/heroVisual.js` — set `HERO_VISUAL_MODE` to `'placeholder'` or `'flow-diagram'`; configure slide images in `HERO_SLIDES`
- Config menu visibility: `src/config/siteConfig.js` — set `VITE_SHOW_CONFIG_MENU=true` in `.env.local` to show (hidden by default)
- Site access gate: enabled by default (`Summer2026` unless `VITE_SITE_PASSWORD` is set). Set `VITE_SITE_ACCESS=false` to disable. Client-side only — not real security.
- Static assets go in `public/` (e.g. `public/images/`)

## UI patterns

- Use `PlaceholderImage` for image slots without assets yet; use `ProjectImage` for project cards/pages (handles image vs placeholder).
- Hover effects on cards only for clickable links (`a.theme-card`), not static content cards.
- Interactive menus (theme selector, mobile nav) must work on tap — use click/toggle, not hover-only.
- Avoid layout shift: reserve fixed space for elements that change size on active/hover states.
- Carousels: use `theme-carousel-control` for prev/next buttons; provide pause for auto-advancing content; respect `useReducedMotion()`.

## Hero slider

- Research / Design / Impact tabs in `HeroFlowDiagram.jsx` control slide pagination.
- Auto-cycles every 7 seconds with a visible pause/play control; auto-advance is disabled when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.
- Pagination icons: `SquareUserRound`, `LayoutDashboard`, `Rocket`.

## Scope and quality

- Minimize diff scope — only change what the task requires.
- Match existing naming, file structure, and styling patterns.
- Do not commit or push unless explicitly asked.
- Run `npm run build` to verify changes compile before finishing.

## Code & Component Quality

- Write clean, modular, and reusable components. Avoid monolithic files.
- Use semantic HTML tags exclusively (`<main>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`) instead of generic nested `<div>` wrappers.
- Optimize images using lazy loading and responsive source sets.

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA)

This site targets **WCAG 2.2 Level AA**. Treat accessibility as a requirement, not a polish step.

### Color & contrast

- **Normal text** (below 18px / 14px bold): minimum **4.5:1** contrast against its background.
- **Large text** (18px+ or 14px+ bold): minimum **3:1**.
- **UI components / focus indicators**: minimum **3:1** (WCAG 1.4.11).
- Never pair `theme-text-subtle` with essential reading content — reserve it for non-critical hints only.
- Use `theme-text-muted` for captions, dates, and secondary copy; use `text-sm` (14px) minimum for readable content.
- Use `theme-link` for links (includes underline); do not rely on color alone.
- Primary buttons use `--color-btn-primary-fg` — dusk/dark themes use dark text on light accent backgrounds.
- When adding tokens, verify contrast on **all four themes** against both `--color-bg` and `--color-surface`.

### Typography

- Body copy: `text-base` (16px) or `text-sm` (14px).
- Do **not** use `text-xs` (12px) for essential content (captions, attributions, menu descriptions).
- `text-xs` is acceptable only for uppercase badges/tags with sufficient contrast on badge backgrounds (`theme-badge`, not `theme-accent-bg-subtle`).

### Interaction & keyboard

- Every interactive element must have a visible `:focus-visible` state (global styles in `index.css`).
- Touch targets: minimum **44×44px** preferred (`min-w-11 min-h-11`); WCAG 2.5.8 minimum is 24×24px.
- All icons must use `DecorativeIcon` / `aria-hidden="true"` when decorative, or explicit `aria-label` when functional.
- Custom widgets (carousels, menus) need full keyboard support and correct ARIA (`role`, `aria-label`, `aria-selected`, `aria-live`).
- Site-wide skip link lives in `Layout.jsx` → `#main-content`. Workshop has its own skip link.

### Motion

- Use `useReducedMotion()` from `src/hooks/useReducedMotion.js` for auto-playing carousels and animations.
- Global `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` rules in `index.css` disable smooth scroll and transitions.
- Auto-advancing content **must** include a pause control (WCAG 2.2.2).

### Pages & structure

- Set unique page titles via `useDocumentMeta()` on every route.
- One `<h1>` per page; do not skip heading levels.
- Images require descriptive `alt` text; decorative images use empty alt or `aria-hidden`.
- Use `SrOnly` for screen-reader-only live regions and labels.

### Before shipping UI changes

1. Check contrast in all four themes for any new text/background pairings.
2. Tab through the changed UI — focus order and visibility must make sense.
3. Confirm touch targets on mobile-sized controls.
4. Run `npm run build`.

## Deployment

- Vercel serves the Vite build from `dist/`.
- `vercel.json` includes SPA rewrites for client-side routing — preserve when editing config.
